title: Yreka High varsity VB squad falls to West Valley in three sets at home
text: Yreka High varsity VB squad falls to West Valley in three sets at home Comment   By Daily News staff Posted Oct. 14, 2015 at 1:42 PM By Daily News staff Posted Oct. 14, 2015 at 1:42 PM YREKA The Yreka High varsity volleyball team fell to West Valley 23-25, 20-25, 24-26 in Northern Athletic League action at home on Tuesday. Katie Bennett, photo 2, led Yreka with nine kills, 18 digs, and eight service points. Ashley Cox had 22 assists, while Taylor Callahan had four blocks. Yreka fell to 14-13 overall and 1-2 in the NAL, while West Valley improved to 22-3 overall and 3-0 in the NAL. The Yreka High freshman volleyball team downed West Valley at home 25-18, 25-22 on Tuesday to improve to 3-0 in the NAL. The Lady Miner junior varsity squad fell to West Valley 25-11, 25-12 On Thursday, Yreka is at Lassen in NAL action By Daily News staff   By Daily News staff
